g.text: DynamoDB Operations
* PutItem - Creates new or replaces existing (with same Primary Key)
Consumes WCUs
* UpdateItem - Update existing item's attributes or add a new item if does not exist
* Conditional Writes - Accept a write/update/delete only if conditions are met, otherwise returns an error.
Writing Data
* GetItem - Read based on Primary key
Eventually Consistent Read or Strongly Consistent Read
- ProjectionExpression can be specified to retrieve only certain attributes
* Query - Returns items based on KeyConditionExpression/FilterExpression
* Scan - Scan the entire table and then filter out data (inefficient)
Reading Data
* DeleteItem - Delete an individual item
Ability to perform conditional delete
* DeleteTable - Delete a whole table and all items items
Deleting Data
* BatchWriteItem - 25 PutItem or DeleteItem in one call
Upto 16MB data written, 400KB per item (no update only put or delete)
* BatchGetItem - Return items from one or more tables
Upto 100 items, up to 16 MB of data
Batch Operations
** PartiQL - SQL - compatible query language for DynamoDB
